# Cypress Standards

## Structure

- Page objects in `cypress/pages/` — specs never contain raw selectors
- API helpers in `cypress/utils/apiClient.js`
- Auth via `cypress/utils/auth.js` using `cy.session()` + API login
- Factories in `cypress/fixtures/factories/` — no live credentials or JWTs
- Package overview: `cypress/README.md`

## Auth

- Prefer API login inside `cy.session()` for speed (`cy.loginViaSession(user)`)
- Register/login specs use UI only; all other P0 specs use session + API setup
- Never commit session cache or tokens

## Selectors

- Follow ADR-003 hierarchy: role → label → placeholder → text
- Selectors live in page objects only

## Reporting

- Allure via `@shelex/cypress-allure-plugin` in `cypress.config.js`
- Results output to `cypress/reports/allure-results/`

## Documentation

- JSDoc on all exports in `utils/`, `fixtures/factories/`, and `support/commands.js`
- JSDoc class header on each page object; method docs only for composite or non-obvious behavior
- No JSDoc on spec files — see `.cursor/rules/general.mdc`

## Conventions

- Specs: `tests/**/*.cy.js`
- Run: `npm test` from `cypress/` (requires Conduit up — see package README)
- CI: `retries=0` for flakiness measurement (`npx cypress run --config retries=0`)
